Behaviour: Rest, play, travel from (Crossing above road)

Unnamed: 12: The individual was moving across the trees on the right side of the trail (looking from the entrance). Once it spotted us, it paused to watch us for a moment. Later it continued until it crossed the trail via trees right above our heads showing no fear. It then wondered further into the forest.

The individual was moving from tree to tree at fast pace on the left side of the trail (looking from the entrance). It could have possibly been the same one we noticed earlier... however the first one was slow as if looking for food, while this one seemed in a rush.

First we noticed one individual on the right side of the road. It watched us with curosity for quite some time while taking some rather relaxed poses (as can be seen on photos shared). It eventually moved further into the forest after having heard a few calls from the langurs on the other side of the road. About the same time we spotted, one by one, four more individuals on the left side of the road. They were scattred around on various trees but slowly moving towards the same one tree. Eventually we could see two of them sit next to each other to relax and eat leaves. The other two stayed close on the nearby tree. After 15mins we left them there and moved on.
Unnamed: 13: Numerous troops of macaques were everywhere to be seen also nearby the langurs. The weather was nice and sunny after a heavy rain in the mid day.
